. erm.... I mean Adventuer/Risktaker.... I am hell bent on takin the hard way in, but alas i need to pick a lock... how on earth or norath do I raise my skill in lockpicking?  How do I use this abbility?  Thanx in advance for your answers all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-Taim M'hael<br>
 Rogu.. erm  Adventuer/Risktaker<br>
 32nd Level/Zebwhatever server  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utannblackpoint.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tann Blackpoint</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/10/01 12:01:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bruning Rapier Quest</span><hr size=1> Zeb zerver eh? Shoot a tell to Tannwindar if you need advice on anything. =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uglinlor00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glinlor00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/10/01 10:41:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bruning Rapier Quest</span><hr size=1> Well you need a lock pick skill of 120+ i think to pick that lock, my Rogue got the quest done at 18th level, with abit of help from my wizard, and at one point another rogue who was doing the same quest, she opend the door for me, I went in and camped my Rogue their, came back on the next day, got the bag and petitioned for help that I was stuck in a room with no way out.<br>
<br>
When the guide got their, he couldent see anything in the room so he let me out, not that it matterd, because I had asked anoter rogue to come let me out, I just wanted to see what would happen.  Intresting ea? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usilentheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silentheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/10/01 11:24:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bruning Rapier Quest</span><hr size=1> Steps to Raising Good Ole LockPicking:<br>
1) Go to your local Rogue or Bard guild and purches lock picks.<br>
2) Head to Befallen and proceede to click on the first floor locked door for a few hours.  (Dump some practice points in lock pick to help you get a head start)<br>
3) Get Pick lock to 120, then head to the Door needed to be picked for the quest.  (I believe the Befallen door will get you to 120, can't remember, been awhile since I raised Pick lock for the quest.)<br>
<br>
Hope this helps ya out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulemacdushae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lemac Dushae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/10/01 4:12:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bruning Rapier Quest</span><hr size=1> <br>
Any door you can pick will serve to skill up to 210 on.<br>
<br>
The door in Hallard's needs a 122 to unlock. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/01 3:49:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bruning Rapier Quest</span><hr size=1> Unless they've fixed it, Befallen needs an 11 skill to open the doors.  If you got the skill at 6th or so, bump it up a few points to 11.  There are (were?) no doors that could be opened with a skill under 11. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueriswarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eriswarrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/01 11:26:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bruning Rapier Quest</span><hr size=1> You can use the Befallen door to get up to at lease 150. BTW you can go to Sol A, since you are in the neighborhood and click on the first pendulum and raise you disarm traps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukehvrynne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kehvrynne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/12/01 8:01:00 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bruning Rapier Quest</span><hr size=1> You can practice your Pick Lock skill all the way to it's maximum cap in Befallen.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3149.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3226.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3248.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3248.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3248.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3248.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Root Cellar<option value="thesaf